{
  "texts": [
    "Examples of such clauses are comprised in Synthesia's terms of service (point 10 -Software License and Content).",
    "A second safe measure taken is the Privacy Policy, which regulates a notice and take down system, together with the discretionary right of the provider to erase the unlawful collected data: 'where content includes personal information about private individuals this will be further regulated by our Privacy Policy, DPA, or other individual agreement' (Synthesia, n.d.).",
    "In what concerns the intentional training of GenAI with personal data, the provider is liable when infringing GDPR's provisions.",
    "Even if this regulation is already well known in all industries, worldwide, breaches still happen.",
    "Recently, an AI software developer has been fined by the Italian data protection authority for unlawful processing of biometric data, used to train facial recognition AI (European Data Protection Board, 2022)."
  ]
}